                "value": 0.999
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 32-cm2 rotating target",
                "consisted of the enriched isotope Am-243 (99.9%)",
                "deposited as AmO(2) onto 1.5-um Ti foils to a",
                "thickness of 0.36 mg/cm2 of 243Am, the foils were",
                "covered by a C-layer 35 ug/cm2.",
                "Each of six targets had an area of 5.3 cm2 in the shape",
                "of an arc segment with an angular extension of 60 degr",
                "and an average radius of 60 mm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MCPLT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A 4-cm x 12-cm semiconductor detector array",
                "with 12 vertical position-sensitive strips surrounded",
                "by eight 4-cm x 4-cm side detectors without position",
                "sensitivity, forming a box open to the front (beam)",
                "side. The position-averaged detection efficiency for",
                "full-energy alpha-particles emitted in the decays of",
                "implanted nuclei was 87%."
              ]
            }
          ],
